<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 30 at 3:22PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
northeastern Appomattox and Buckingham Counties through 345 PM EDT...
At 322 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Toga, or 7 miles southwest of Buckingham, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Buckingham...
Dillwyn...
Bent Creek...
New Canton...
Toga...
Centenary...
and Sheppards.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
